In [[mathematics]], '''Tate's isogeny theorem''', proved by {{harvs|txt|last=Tate|year=1966|authorlink=John Tate}}, states that two [[abelian varieties]] over a [[finite field]] are [[isogeny|isogeneous]] if and only if their [[Tate module]]s are isomorphic (as [[Galois representation]]s).

