In [[mathematics]], '''Weber's theorem''', named after [[Heinrich Martin Weber]], is a result on [[algebraic curve]]s. It states the following.

: Consider two non-singular curves ''C'' and ''C''&prime; having the same [[genus (mathematics)|genus]] ''g'' > 1. If there is a rational [[Correspondence (mathematics)|correspondence]] &phi; between ''C'' and ''C''&prime;, then &phi; is a [[birational transformation]].

