In [[number theory]], '''octic reciprocity''' is a [[reciprocity law]] relating the residues of 8th powers [[modular arithmetic|modulo]] [[prime number|primes]], analogous to the [[law of quadratic reciprocity]].

There is a [[rational reciprocity law]] for 8th powers, due to Williams.  Define the symbol (''x''|''p'')<sub>''k''</sub> to be +1 if ''x'' is a ''k''-th power modulo the prime ''p'' and -1 otherwise.  Let ''p'' and ''q'' be distinct primes congruent to 1 modulo 8, such that (''p''|''q'') = (''q''|''p'') = +1.  Let ''p'' = ''a''<sup>2</sup> + ''b''<sup>2</sup> = ''c''<sup>2</sup> + 2''d''<sup>2</sup> and ''q'' = ''A''<sup>2</sup> + ''B''<sup>2</sup> = ''C''<sup>2</sup> + 2''D''<sup>2</sup>, with ''aA'' odd.  Then

:<math> (p|q)_8 = (q|p)_8 = (aB-bA|q)_4 (cD-dC|q)_2 \ .</math>

